    {
      "type": "note",
      "spec_version": "2.1",
      "id": "note--analysis-summary",
      "created": "2026-03-31T22:29:05.000Z",
      "modified": "2026-03-31T22:29:05.000Z",
      "content": "The Salo Hotfix campaign uses a 5-layer attack chain designed to evade all AV/EDR detection. The DLL side-loading technique abuses a legitimately signed Python Software Foundation binary. The XOR key o6utydhcgf75ks and C# namespace CybersecurityMuseum.Workshop are strong indicators for tracking this campaign. The monitoring beacon pattern (/stats/salo/monitor.php?q=[a|b|c]) provides visibility into the operator tracking execution success at each stage.",
